Lorec, Wandering Judge <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uxsatyrx.showPublicProfile?language=EN>xsatyrx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 31<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/7/02 2:09:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=205.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_lightbulb.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: TLC Quest message board?</span><hr size=1> My thoughts on this is this...I believe that it is completely up to the seller. I do not believe in a standard price for ANY item.<br>
<br>
If someone is wanting to charge so much...so be it. Either they will find a buyer or not. I find this just and fair in every sense of the words just like i find it just and fair that some sellers choose not to sell to certain people or races...in my opinion this can be RPing. It may not be, but at any rate, I find it the RIGHT of the seller to ask for whatever price he sees fit.<br>
<br>
Some may argue that this isnt fair...I find statements like this to be one of whiners. For if they didnt make the effort to get these pieces themselves...if it is easier for one class or level than another to obtain the item, that is way 'the cookie crumbles'. Like real life, the world of EQ isnt always fair and that i do find cool. If it was any different i believe my experiences with the game wouldnt be half as enjoyable.)<br>
<br>
